Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a #pot{} of
water for the eggs.

Roughly chop the @Chives{5%g} (use scissors if you prefer).

Lay the @Irish Bacon{130%g} rashers in a single layer on a lined #baking tray{}.

Bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden brown and crispy, ~{10-15%mins}.
> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon
> thoroughly.

Add the @Apple Cider Vinegar{1%sachet} to the pot of @Water{to taste}. Crack
each @Egg{4}(2 per person) into separate #small bowls{}.

Swirl the water with a #spoon{} to create a whirlpool. Drop the eggs into the
centre of the whirlpool. Lower the heat to a simmer.

Poach until the white is firm, ~{2-3%mins}. Remove each egg with a
#slotted spoon{}. Season with @Salt{to taste} and @Pepper{to taste}.

Alternatively, to fry the eggs, place a #pan{} on medium-high heat with a
drizzle of @Oil{to taste}. Fry until the white is cooked and the yolk is your
desired firmness, ~{4-5%mins}.

Warm the @Hollandaise Sauce{100%g} in a pot over medium heat. Season to taste
with salt and pepper.

Warm the @Ciabatta{2} in the oven for ~{2-3%mins}.

Halve the @Avocado{1} and remove the pit. Scoop out the flesh onto a
#board{}. Thinly slice lengthways.

Halve the ciabattas. Top with bacon and avocado, followed by an egg.

Drizzle over the hollandaise. Sprinkle over the chives.